{
  "stem": "2758.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So my mother hired a tutor for me to teach Polish and also curriculum-- geography and math, and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was-- It was not a nice country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I was used to being in Holland, which is a wonderful country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But that was the way it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In May or April of 1935-- we were just a few months there-- there was a pogrom, not in Radom, but on the outskirts, about 20 miles away from Radom.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It was Passover, Easter, and they killed a lot of people, a lot of Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And that had a terrible effect on all of us because we really did not expect a thing like this to happen in a democratic country.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But that apparently is the way it is, and so you, you have to-- if you can't go anyplace else, you've got to be there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We then moved to a different apartment in the same building where in aunts lived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And there, we had a little closer contact.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "My mother's sister-- she had two sisters living in the same apartment house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So we, we had cousins and aunts and uncles, and life was a little nicer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I didn't have to be the caretaker exclusively.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "My aunt was there, and my other aunt was there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So it was better.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "In 1939 in September, the war broke out, and we were bombed in, in, in a few days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And at the first time that you experience such a thing, it's devastating.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It didn't bomb our house, but next to us on the same street.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And, and then we thought-- then Warsaw fell in six weeks, I think, and the Germans moved into Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "First thing they did, we had to register.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And we--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
